<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-22T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-22T16:00:00-05:00" n="1033" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1033">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.92/12–2245: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Political Adviser in Siam</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Tost</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-22T16:00:00-05:00">December 22, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>80. Dept believes US should not resume diplomatic relations
                                immediately on treaty signing to avoid association therewith, but
                                equally should avoid long delay. Present view is that Jan 1 would be
                                suitable day, but feel we must clear with Brit so that both may act
                                same day, but with US technically in advance in view previous
                                deferment. Please advise Dept immediately your judgment as to most
                                suitable time.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>